HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton ƙaruwar sabbin cututtuka da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa akwai karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan 'yan kasarta da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne ke fama da cutar a ƙasar.
An samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke wakiltar canji daga baya.
A al'ada, HIV yana yaɗuwa da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wurin ƙarin jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Shekara bayan shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da HIV da AIDS a China ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i ta zama babban batu a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An yi wa luwadi yancin yin jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT har yanzu yana da yawa.
Domin ƙa'idodin ƙasar da suka fi na zamani, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su yi aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka da ake yaɗawa suna zuwa ne daga rashin kāriya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin da take yi na magance matsalar.
